---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '~/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Policy — Soothemade"
  description="How the studio handles privacy, returns, and the small print."
>
  <Nav />
  <article class="policy">
    <div class="eyebrow">— the small print —</div>
    <h1><em>Plain</em> policy.</h1>

    <div class="body">
      <p class="lede">
        The umbrella site does not sell anything directly. Each line has
        its own policy. Below is the plain version, written for a person.
        Each line's site has the legal version, written for a court.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        We collect as little as possible. If you leave an email on the
        letter form, we keep it in a list and send a letter every other
        Sunday. We do not sell it. We do not trade it. We do not enrich
        it. We do not run third-party tracking pixels on this site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Server logs from Cloudflare exist (this site runs on Cloudflare
        Workers). They retain IP addresses for a short window for
        abuse-prevention purposes. We do not look at them unless
        something is broken.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unsubscribe whenever. Every letter has a one-click link at the
        bottom. The next letter, you are off the list.
      </p>

      <h2>Returns and refunds</h2>
      <p>
        The umbrella shop does not sell anything. Products are sold by
        each line (currently <a class="ext" href="https://notes.soothemade.com" rel="noopener">Soothemade Notes</a>), each with its
        own return policy. See the line's site for specifics.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not set marketing cookies. The platform may set
        small technical cookies for the site to function. We do not run
        analytics that profile you.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This site is not directed at children. We do not knowingly
        collect information from anyone under 16.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, we will note the date below and write
        about the change in the letter. Last updated: 2026-05-20.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@soothemade.com">hello@soothemade.com</a>. We read everything.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    max-width: var(--container-narrow);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 72px var(--sp-7) 80px;
  }
  .eyebrow { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--fs-4xl);
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .body { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink); }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 36px 0 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .body p { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .body a { color: var(--accent); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .policy { padding: 48px var(--sp-5) 64px; }
    h1 { font-size: 38px; }
    .body { font-size: 16px; }
  }
</style>
